            . I am assistant to the Solicitor for the Mint. I have here the bad money produced on the trial of the three men alluded to. I produce five, which I believe to be five of the eight taken from Connell's pocket. During the course of the former trial, I selected three upon which I supported the indictment. I know these five because I have marked them with a cross, I marked them on the day I took them, in the prosence of Brock and Pelham.</p>
